1
00:00:01,140 --> 00:00:03,740
(Episode 81)

2
00:00:07,950 --> 00:00:10,120
(CEO Chae Hwa Young)

3
00:00:14,250 --> 00:00:16,760
Welcome, Oh Jang Mi. You evil witch.

4
00:00:18,890 --> 00:00:21,460
You knew it was me?

5
00:00:21,530 --> 00:00:22,630
Of course.

6
00:00:22,630 --> 00:00:25,500
Did you think I didn't know
you posed as Seo Rin and betrayed me?

7
00:00:25,600 --> 00:00:29,000
Chae Hwa Young, it takes a lot of nerve
to crawl out here with that face.

8
00:00:29,670 --> 00:00:32,440
As if framing Professor Kang Nam Bong
for your crime wasn't enough,

9
00:00:32,500 --> 00:00:33,910
now you're pinning it on Ssangkal, too?

10
00:00:33,910 --> 00:00:36,440
How dare you turn around and slander me?

11
00:00:37,080 --> 00:00:39,640
How dare you get me into this mess?

12
00:00:40,450 --> 00:00:42,710
When I think about the detention center
you put me in,

13
00:00:42,780 --> 00:00:44,720
I could just rip you to shreds.

14
00:00:45,350 --> 00:00:47,250
You're just running wild,
completely out of line.

15
00:00:47,320 --> 00:00:49,520
You're a murderer.
Who are you to threaten me?

16
00:00:50,020 --> 00:00:53,260
Just you wait. You'll end up right back
in prison, where you belong.

17
00:00:53,320 --> 00:00:56,430
- Shut up!
- Enjoy your vacation while you can.

18
00:00:56,930 --> 00:00:59,260
Because I'm about to expose you
for hurting Seo Rin,

19
00:00:59,530 --> 00:01:01,170
and I'm going to throw you
right back in prison.

20
00:01:01,270 --> 00:01:05,300
You're a con artist who left your family
to save your own skin by becoming Seo Rin.

21
00:01:05,370 --> 00:01:07,540
- What did you say?
- You impersonated Seo Rin,

22
00:01:07,540 --> 00:01:10,140
living lavishly and spending money
like it was nothing.

23
00:01:10,180 --> 00:01:11,910
You're the one who should be in cuffs!

24
00:01:11,980 --> 00:01:13,750
How dare a con artist like you
threaten me?

25
00:01:13,750 --> 00:01:15,310
You think I didn't consider that...

26
00:01:15,310 --> 00:01:16,710
when I entered your house
to take you down?

27
00:01:18,150 --> 00:01:20,120
- To take me down?
- That's right.

28
00:01:20,190 --> 00:01:22,350
I'm here to take you down
for murdering my dad.

29
00:01:22,590 --> 00:01:25,620
How can impersonating Seo Rin
even compare to murder?

30
00:01:25,890 --> 00:01:28,690
Isn't it rich, for a murderer like you
to point fingers at me?

31
00:01:28,760 --> 00:01:29,760
Shut up!

32
00:01:30,500 --> 00:01:33,530
You've got some serious nerve.
You just wait.

33
00:01:34,030 --> 00:01:37,770
Just sit back and watch
how I'm going to make your family pay.

34
00:01:37,840 --> 00:01:38,870
Chae Hwa Young.

35
00:01:38,870 --> 00:01:41,910
If you touch my family,
you think I'll just let it happen?

36
00:01:42,770 --> 00:01:43,840
I'm so scared.

37
00:01:48,350 --> 00:01:50,620
Oh, Seo Rin. My sweet daughter.

38
00:01:53,350 --> 00:01:54,350
Keep your mouth shut.

39
00:01:54,850 --> 00:01:58,490
Or else I'll take Oh Tae Sook's shop
down to the ground.

40
00:02:01,430 --> 00:02:02,560
You're suffocating me.

41
00:02:05,760 --> 00:02:08,870
You came straight to the office
without getting any rest?

42
00:02:09,570 --> 00:02:10,800
Yes, I did, General Manager Kang.

43
00:02:12,040 --> 00:02:13,470
I came because I was worried
about the company.

44
00:02:13,970 --> 00:02:14,970
Have a seat, General Manager Kang.

45
00:02:17,940 --> 00:02:19,140
Seo Rin, come and sit down too.

46
00:02:20,550 --> 00:02:24,180
Our first priority is getting the company
back on track, don't you think?

47
00:02:28,420 --> 00:02:31,760
What's going on with CEO Chae?

48
00:02:35,160 --> 00:02:36,760
Dad, you said you wanted to talk?

49
00:02:37,060 --> 00:02:39,800
Actually, I have something to ask you.
Come and have a seat.

50
00:02:44,670 --> 00:02:46,140
It's about CEO Chae.

51
00:02:46,200 --> 00:02:50,310
Tell me everything you know
about what happened with that case.

52
00:02:50,980 --> 00:02:53,610
You're asking
because you're also suspicious...

53
00:02:53,910 --> 00:02:55,710
that CEO Chae was freed
after the "real culprit" confessed, right?

54
00:02:56,880 --> 00:02:59,320
Hey, enough with the questions!
Just tell me what happened.

55
00:03:00,220 --> 00:03:01,990
Okay, here's the timeline of events.

56
00:03:02,590 --> 00:03:04,660
CEO Chae was
in the hotel's underground parking garage,

57
00:03:04,890 --> 00:03:07,390
where she pushed Oh Bok Gil,
knocking him unconscious.

58
00:03:07,860 --> 00:03:09,390
Then, on a country road, you supposedly...

59
00:03:09,630 --> 00:03:12,130
hit Oh Bok Gil with your car,
which resulted in his death.

60
00:03:12,660 --> 00:03:14,900
Those are the objective facts of the case
as we knew them.

61
00:03:15,130 --> 00:03:19,200
But then the "real culprit" confessed
to killing Oh Bok Gil...

62
00:03:19,340 --> 00:03:21,640
- and turned himself in?
- Yes.

63
00:03:22,310 --> 00:03:25,910
The story is that Oh Bok Gil got up
in the parking garage just fine...

64
00:03:26,140 --> 00:03:28,350
and then started blackmailing
CEO Chae for money.

65
00:03:28,650 --> 00:03:31,120
CEO Chae gave him some cash
to get rid of him.

66
00:03:31,120 --> 00:03:32,350
But Ssangkal saw it,

67
00:03:32,650 --> 00:03:36,450
followed him, killed him,
and then left his body on a road.

68
00:03:36,450 --> 00:03:37,490
That's their story.

69
00:03:37,820 --> 00:03:38,860
Unbelievable.

70
00:03:39,090 --> 00:03:42,330
But for you to be passing by
on that same road at that exact moment...

71
00:03:42,460 --> 00:03:44,300
and end up hitting Oh Bok Gil?

72
00:03:44,300 --> 00:03:46,000
It just doesn't add up, right?

73
00:03:47,270 --> 00:03:50,170
I need to see CEO Chae.

74
00:03:50,770 --> 00:03:53,810
Dad, you don't have feelings
for her still, right?

75
00:03:59,110 --> 00:04:02,580
Seo Rin, aren't you happy to see me
after everything I've been through?

76
00:04:03,250 --> 00:04:04,720
Why the long face?

77
00:04:07,690 --> 00:04:11,160
Oh Jang Mi.
I need you until I find the real Seo Rin.

78
00:04:11,820 --> 00:04:14,690
You're on borrowed time. Just you wait.

79
00:04:16,460 --> 00:04:19,000
Mom, why are you looking at me like that?

80
00:04:20,230 --> 00:04:22,270
You must have had a really hard time
in the detention center.

81
00:04:22,670 --> 00:04:26,000
- You look like crap.
- Shut up!

82
00:04:26,440 --> 00:04:27,910
Goodness, you scared me!

83
00:04:28,640 --> 00:04:32,210
Knowing you, I'm surprised you're here
instead of at a skin clinic.

84
00:04:32,280 --> 00:04:33,410
What's gotten into you?

85
00:04:33,480 --> 00:04:36,280
Did jail make you a changed woman?

86
00:04:37,750 --> 00:04:38,750
Ma Seo Rin...

87
00:04:39,950 --> 00:04:41,720
I bet you wrote lots of apology letters.

88
00:04:42,120 --> 00:04:46,020
In dramas, if you write enough of those,
they reduce your sentence.

89
00:04:46,360 --> 00:04:48,630
- I guess that worked for you?
- Will you knock it off?

90
00:04:49,230 --> 00:04:51,200
Watch your mouth
in front of General Manager Kang.

91
00:04:51,300 --> 00:04:54,270
Why are you yelling at me?
Are you even my mother?

92
00:04:54,570 --> 00:04:58,340
Aren't you being too harsh
to your daughter?

93
00:04:58,700 --> 00:04:59,800
Right, Jun Ho?

94
00:05:02,740 --> 00:05:05,680
Mom, are you taking something out on me
now that you're out of jail?

95
00:05:06,280 --> 00:05:08,150
I'm the one who should be angry.

96
00:05:08,150 --> 00:05:09,450
Do you have any idea...

97
00:05:09,450 --> 00:05:11,180
how much people were judging me,
calling you a murderer?

98
00:05:11,850 --> 00:05:14,550
You have no idea how hard it was
putting up with that humiliation.

99
00:05:15,620 --> 00:05:16,620
Shit!

100
00:05:17,990 --> 00:05:20,830
She even acts just like Seo Rin.
A true twin.

101
00:05:21,160 --> 00:05:25,060
So that's how you tricked me, Oh Jang Mi.
You little witch.

102
00:05:25,260 --> 00:05:28,170
Are you cursing me out in your head?
Why are you looking at me like that?

103
00:05:29,000 --> 00:05:30,070
That's enough.

104
00:05:30,840 --> 00:05:32,300
I guess I'm just on edge
because I'm so tired.

105
00:05:32,600 --> 00:05:34,910
What are you going to do about Oh Jang Mi,

106
00:05:35,170 --> 00:05:36,410
the one who reported you for murder?

107
00:05:36,610 --> 00:05:40,210
We should sue for defamation and damages.

108
00:05:40,510 --> 00:05:42,510
But that would only create a media frenzy,

109
00:05:42,880 --> 00:05:44,380
so I need to think it over.

110
00:05:44,850 --> 00:05:46,720
What if I met with Oh Jang Mi?

111
00:05:48,050 --> 00:05:49,490
That sounds interesting.

112
00:05:49,620 --> 00:05:50,860
By all means, go meet her,

113
00:05:51,020 --> 00:05:52,920
and be sure to tell me
all about it, Jun Ho.

114
00:05:55,830 --> 00:05:58,000
(CEO Chae Hwa Young)

115
00:06:01,800 --> 00:06:04,570
Jun Ho, stay out of it.
I don't want to blow this up any further.

116
00:06:05,700 --> 00:06:09,910
The PR Department will be sending out
a major press release about my innocence,

117
00:06:10,410 --> 00:06:12,340
so let's just leave it at that.

118
00:06:13,280 --> 00:06:14,980
Understood. Alright then...

119
00:06:17,820 --> 00:06:19,080
Now that you've been released,

120
00:06:19,220 --> 00:06:22,350
please expedite my marriage
to Director Ma.

121
00:06:27,460 --> 00:06:29,390
They're suing you for damages, Jang Mi?

122
00:06:29,830 --> 00:06:31,360
That's just ridiculous.

123
00:06:31,430 --> 00:06:34,570
I thought I had her, but I never expected
her to pull something like this.

124
00:06:34,870 --> 00:06:35,930
I'm so furious.

125
00:06:36,700 --> 00:06:40,040
I can't believe Ssangkal is
claiming to be the killer.

126
00:06:40,340 --> 00:06:43,840
Even with a confession, he'll get
at least ten years since it's murder.

127
00:06:43,910 --> 00:06:45,510
I don't understand why he'd do that.

128
00:06:45,610 --> 00:06:47,880
She must've either paid him off
or threatened him.

129
00:06:48,310 --> 00:06:51,720
That Chae Hwa Young is relentless.
The sight of her face makes me sick.

130
00:06:51,850 --> 00:06:55,090
Anyway, now that CEO Chae knows
who you really are,

131
00:06:55,390 --> 00:06:56,990
you need to be extra careful.

132
00:07:02,490 --> 00:07:04,200
(CEO Chae Hwa Young)

133
00:07:04,660 --> 00:07:07,430
Professor Kang,
you must have been so worried.

134
00:07:08,570 --> 00:07:11,800
Goodness, that place was
no place for a human being.

135
00:07:11,940 --> 00:07:13,040
CEO Chae.

136
00:07:14,370 --> 00:07:16,410
Tell me the truth.

137
00:07:16,740 --> 00:07:17,740
Excuse me?

138
00:07:18,440 --> 00:07:21,080
- The truth about what?
- The culprit supposedly confessed.

139
00:07:23,180 --> 00:07:26,520
But they said you had Oh Bok Gil's phone.

140
00:07:29,120 --> 00:07:32,060
So how could someone else have confessed?

141
00:07:33,720 --> 00:07:36,790
You're the one who called me
and told me to go there.

142
00:07:37,730 --> 00:07:40,900
Be honest with me.

143
00:07:41,330 --> 00:07:42,330
Professor Kang.

144
00:07:44,670 --> 00:07:46,900
I think there's been
a serious misunderstanding.

145
00:07:47,570 --> 00:07:49,340
I must say, I'm quite hurt.

146
00:07:49,340 --> 00:07:51,040
I'm the one who should feel hurt!

147
00:07:51,480 --> 00:07:53,640
I know for a fact
that I got a call from you,

148
00:07:54,050 --> 00:07:55,480
and that's why I went there.

149
00:07:55,880 --> 00:07:57,420
You laid Oh Bok Gil in my path,

150
00:07:57,420 --> 00:07:59,880
knowing I would come that way, didn't you?

151
00:08:00,180 --> 00:08:01,650
You did it to frame me.

152
00:08:02,020 --> 00:08:04,890
- Professor Kang!
- There's a limit to your backstabbing.

153
00:08:07,590 --> 00:08:08,790
From now on,

154
00:08:09,430 --> 00:08:10,700
don't ever act as if you know me again.

155
00:08:11,400 --> 00:08:14,330
Professor Kang. Please, just hear me out.

156
00:08:14,330 --> 00:08:15,700
I'll consider everything...

157
00:08:16,000 --> 00:08:18,970
that's happened up to now
the price I had to pay for loving you,

158
00:08:19,600 --> 00:08:21,340
and I won't bring it up again.

159
00:08:21,610 --> 00:08:22,640
But...

160
00:08:24,310 --> 00:08:26,210
this feeling of disgust
will stay with me for a long time.

161
00:08:26,940 --> 00:08:28,180
Meeting you...

162
00:08:29,310 --> 00:08:30,780
is something I truly regret.

163
00:08:35,750 --> 00:08:39,920
Professor Kang!
Nam Bong, please, just hear me out.

164
00:08:39,990 --> 00:08:43,130
- Let go of me.
- No, you can't just leave like this.

165
00:08:43,690 --> 00:08:44,730
Ten minutes is all I need.

166
00:08:44,730 --> 00:08:47,670
No, one minute! Please, just listen to me.

167
00:08:47,730 --> 00:08:49,900
Please, I'm begging you,
just listen to me.

168
00:08:51,000 --> 00:08:52,000
Fine.

169
00:08:54,110 --> 00:08:55,370
Let's hear your excuses.

170
00:08:57,810 --> 00:08:58,810
Nam Bong.

171
00:09:00,310 --> 00:09:01,650
If I'm guilty of anything,

172
00:09:02,580 --> 00:09:04,750
it's the crime of loving you.

173
00:09:07,120 --> 00:09:08,190
You're right.

174
00:09:08,650 --> 00:09:10,250
Everything you said is right.

175
00:09:10,390 --> 00:09:11,790
But you've got it all wrong.

176
00:09:13,320 --> 00:09:16,690
When I called you that day,

177
00:09:17,560 --> 00:09:20,500
it was only because I missed you.

178
00:09:21,070 --> 00:09:22,370
But as it happened,

179
00:09:22,670 --> 00:09:25,000
it seems the real culprit
was listening in on my call.

180
00:09:25,470 --> 00:09:27,740
- What?
- Apparently, that culprit...

181
00:09:28,770 --> 00:09:32,210
was some scumbag
who did dirty work for Manager Lee.

182
00:09:32,780 --> 00:09:35,880
I didn't really know him, but that's
what I found out when I looked into it.

183
00:09:36,510 --> 00:09:38,220
That scumbag was after money,

184
00:09:39,220 --> 00:09:42,690
so after he committed the murder,
he tried to frame me for it...

185
00:09:43,620 --> 00:09:45,490
by planting the cell phone in my safe.

186
00:09:46,190 --> 00:09:47,660
- He...
- Gosh.

187
00:09:48,290 --> 00:09:51,030
- He was after my money, and he...
- Goodness!

188
00:09:52,400 --> 00:09:53,760
Hwa Young!

189
00:09:53,760 --> 00:09:55,370
Snap out of it, Hwa Young!

190
00:10:01,310 --> 00:10:03,570
What? You want me to arrange
for you to meet Jang Mi?

191
00:10:04,280 --> 00:10:07,140
- I do.
- Why do you want to meet Jang Mi?

192
00:10:07,310 --> 00:10:09,510
She filed a false accusation
against the CEO Chae.

193
00:10:09,580 --> 00:10:10,780
I can't just let that slide.

194
00:10:10,950 --> 00:10:12,250
What are you going to do then?

195
00:10:12,420 --> 00:10:14,290
I'm just curious
what kind of woman she is.

196
00:10:14,750 --> 00:10:16,790
Especially since she's the woman you love.

197
00:10:17,020 --> 00:10:18,960
What's the point? Just stay out of it.

198
00:10:19,420 --> 00:10:21,830
Why won't you let me meet
this Oh Jang Mi woman?

199
00:10:22,990 --> 00:10:24,260
Does she even exist?

200
00:10:24,330 --> 00:10:27,030
Come on, would someone
who doesn't exist report CEO Chae?

201
00:10:28,500 --> 00:10:30,500
- Good point.
- But, Jun Ho...

202
00:10:31,470 --> 00:10:34,040
Are you really in love with Ma Seo Rin?

203
00:10:34,310 --> 00:10:36,610
I told you I do.
How many times do I have to tell you?

204
00:10:37,170 --> 00:10:40,210
So you just focus on Jang Mi
and stay out of my business with Seo Rin.

205
00:10:45,020 --> 00:10:47,150
(103,896 dollars)

206
00:10:48,850 --> 00:10:51,020
It's up 117 percent?

207
00:10:51,820 --> 00:10:52,820
What's going on?

208
00:10:55,060 --> 00:10:57,600
Is that phone glued to your hand?

209
00:10:58,100 --> 00:11:00,460
Why have you been staring at it all day,
grinning like a fool?

210
00:11:00,560 --> 00:11:02,200
It's nothing.

211
00:11:02,530 --> 00:11:05,170
There's just so much fun stuff
on phones these days, you know?

212
00:11:09,570 --> 00:11:11,980
- Goodness.
- My goodness, Hwa Young!

213
00:11:12,740 --> 00:11:16,410
My goodness, CEO Chae.
You've wasted away to nothing.

214
00:11:17,050 --> 00:11:19,820
Goodness, your face is so bruised too.

215
00:11:19,820 --> 00:11:20,950
What happened?

216
00:11:21,250 --> 00:11:22,290
I thought you were at the office.

217
00:11:23,290 --> 00:11:25,720
She collapsed at work, so we're
just coming back from getting her an IV.

218
00:11:26,720 --> 00:11:27,830
I'm sorry, Father.

219
00:11:28,460 --> 00:11:29,690
It's okay. You've been through a lot.

220
00:11:30,460 --> 00:11:31,860
But if you had such a hard time,

221
00:11:32,460 --> 00:11:35,000
you should've come straight home to rest.
Why go to the office?

222
00:11:35,570 --> 00:11:36,930
Get her to her room, quickly.

223
00:11:37,570 --> 00:11:38,570
Yes, sir.

224
00:11:51,280 --> 00:11:54,190
Kang Nam Bong won't doubt me now, will he?

225
00:11:54,390 --> 00:11:56,850
After talking to him like that,
I'm sure he's convinced.

226
00:11:56,950 --> 00:11:57,960
That's not good enough.

227
00:11:58,260 --> 00:12:00,890
I'll have to keep a closer eye
on Kang Nam Bong from now on.

228
00:12:02,490 --> 00:12:06,330
If he talks about whether I called him
the day Oh Bok Gil died,

229
00:12:06,430 --> 00:12:07,530
it's going to be a huge headache.

230
00:12:08,670 --> 00:12:11,470
As for the three you were
in the detention center with,

231
00:12:11,770 --> 00:12:13,000
I've taken drastic measures.

232
00:12:13,270 --> 00:12:15,140
Good.
Teach them a lesson they won't forget.

233
00:12:16,010 --> 00:12:18,610
Tearing them limb from limb
wouldn't even be enough.

234
00:12:19,180 --> 00:12:20,880
It makes me tremble with rage
just thinking about it.

235
00:12:37,660 --> 00:12:39,100
That hurts. Be gentle.

236
00:12:39,360 --> 00:12:40,360
Yes.

237
00:12:42,170 --> 00:12:44,940
Right. About that reporter
who wrote the scoop...

238
00:12:45,500 --> 00:12:46,940
Look into them as well.

239
00:12:47,770 --> 00:12:49,110
Actually, I already looked into it.

240
00:12:49,640 --> 00:12:51,440
The reporter is close with Jin Hong Ju.

241
00:12:52,080 --> 00:12:54,750
Jin Hong Ju. I knew it.

242
00:12:55,710 --> 00:12:57,620
I'll deal with her later.

243
00:12:58,580 --> 00:12:59,820
But Kang Hyuk, we have a big problem.

244
00:13:00,450 --> 00:13:02,120
Jun Ho says he's in love with Seo Rin.

245
00:13:02,250 --> 00:13:03,520
He says he's going to marry her.

246
00:13:04,090 --> 00:13:06,520
Now that you've been released,
please expedite my marriage...

247
00:13:06,920 --> 00:13:08,130
to Director Ma.

248
00:13:08,660 --> 00:13:09,730
Jun Ho...

249
00:13:10,230 --> 00:13:12,660
For now, let's focus on
getting the company back on track.

250
00:13:13,130 --> 00:13:15,670
Let's put off talking
about your marriage for now.

251
00:13:18,100 --> 00:13:19,340
Put it off?

252
00:13:19,870 --> 00:13:23,110
Wasn't it your plan
for me to marry Seo Rin?

253
00:13:23,410 --> 00:13:25,380
You even had to talk me into it.

254
00:13:26,180 --> 00:13:27,210
So why all of a sudden...

255
00:13:27,950 --> 00:13:29,110
are you saying this?

256
00:13:29,850 --> 00:13:32,250
That was before I knew
Seo Rin was actually Oh Jang Mi.

257
00:13:32,850 --> 00:13:35,520
Now that I know she's Oh Jang Mi,
it's out of the question.

258
00:13:36,450 --> 00:13:38,160
Is there something you're not telling me?

259
00:13:38,620 --> 00:13:39,620
Jun Ho...

260
00:13:40,020 --> 00:13:41,890
The woman you want to marry...

261
00:13:41,890 --> 00:13:43,330
I'm in love with Ma Seo Rin.

262
00:13:44,830 --> 00:13:47,160
I used to think she was awful.

263
00:13:48,370 --> 00:13:49,930
But the Seo Rin after the accident...

264
00:13:50,670 --> 00:13:53,640
How should I put it?
She's like a completely different person.

265
00:13:54,210 --> 00:13:57,370
I love her for who she is now.

266
00:13:58,380 --> 00:13:59,380
I will...

267
00:13:59,880 --> 00:14:02,010
marry Seo Rin no matter what.

268
00:14:02,780 --> 00:14:03,980
Make it happen.

269
00:14:05,050 --> 00:14:06,150
If you're really my mother.

270
00:14:10,490 --> 00:14:13,520
So, Jun Ho is in love with Oh Jang Mi?

271
00:14:13,990 --> 00:14:15,090
That's what he says.

272
00:14:15,930 --> 00:14:17,900
Should I tell Jun Ho
she's really Oh Jang Mi?

273
00:14:19,300 --> 00:14:21,230
Either way,
to get Dream Group in your hands,

274
00:14:22,000 --> 00:14:24,400
you needed Seo Rin,
Chairman Ma's blood relative, didn't you?

275
00:14:25,270 --> 00:14:27,670
Exactly. I need Chairman Ma's bloodline.

276
00:14:28,070 --> 00:14:30,670
That's why I'm putting up with her,
even though I know she's Oh Jang Mi.

277
00:14:31,510 --> 00:14:34,040
The second we find the real Seo Rin,
Oh Jang Mi is finished.

278
00:14:34,610 --> 00:14:35,780
That insolent brat.

279
00:14:35,980 --> 00:14:39,220
But I have no idea
what happened to the real Seo Rin.

280
00:14:39,850 --> 00:14:43,220
Knowing Seo Rin, if she had woken up,
there's no way she'd be this quiet.

281
00:14:43,890 --> 00:14:47,860
Anyway, as soon as you find Seo Rin,
we'll swap her out with Oh Jang Mi.

282
00:14:48,090 --> 00:14:50,460
Yes, I'll find Seo Rin
as soon as possible.

283
00:14:51,030 --> 00:14:52,030
Manager Lee.

284
00:14:53,960 --> 00:14:55,500
Your first priority is
to take care of Ssangkal.

285
00:14:56,900 --> 00:14:58,400
Eliminate him before he goes to trial.

286
00:14:59,570 --> 00:15:00,570
What?

287
00:15:02,770 --> 00:15:05,680
Isn't that a little too soon?

288
00:15:05,940 --> 00:15:09,550
We can't just sit on a ticking time bomb.
It's now or never.

289
00:15:09,780 --> 00:15:11,320
If he talks, we're all dead.

290
00:15:12,080 --> 00:15:13,580
Then what about finding Seo Rin?

291
00:15:16,450 --> 00:15:18,820
We'll have that mother-daughter duo,
Yeom San Wol and Jin Hong Ju, do it.

292
00:15:19,520 --> 00:15:21,890
And we need to get
San Wol's one percent stake.

293
00:15:24,730 --> 00:15:27,330
So? Did you see CEO Chae?

294
00:15:27,600 --> 00:15:28,670
What did she say?

295
00:15:29,100 --> 00:15:30,470
Let me catch my breath.

296
00:15:30,470 --> 00:15:32,400
I'm just dying to know!

297
00:15:32,570 --> 00:15:35,840
Does she really claim she was released
because she's innocent?

298
00:15:36,670 --> 00:15:38,940
Honestly, I'm not sure what to make of it.

299
00:15:39,180 --> 00:15:41,710
What? What do you mean?

300
00:15:41,850 --> 00:15:43,680
According to CEO Chae,

301
00:15:44,420 --> 00:15:49,390
she said she got into it with Oh Bok Gil
in the hotel parking garage.

302
00:15:49,520 --> 00:15:53,890
She pushed him, and Oh Bok Gil
got a little hurt and demanded money.

303
00:15:53,960 --> 00:15:56,030
So she says all she did
was give him a little cash.

304
00:15:56,530 --> 00:15:58,360
- She what?
- But apparently,

305
00:15:58,630 --> 00:16:02,000
the one who confessed
is someone Manager Lee knows.

306
00:16:02,200 --> 00:16:05,800
He was at the hotel,
saw that Oh Bok Gil had money,

307
00:16:05,970 --> 00:16:07,710
and while in the process of robbing him,

308
00:16:08,070 --> 00:16:09,670
he ended up killing Oh Bok Gil.

309
00:16:10,210 --> 00:16:12,110
Then he dumped the body
in a secluded spot,

310
00:16:12,510 --> 00:16:16,080
hoping that any passing car would hit him.

311
00:16:16,650 --> 00:16:21,150
So, you were just the unlucky one
who got caught up in all of it.

312
00:16:21,790 --> 00:16:23,350
Well...

313
00:16:24,290 --> 00:16:25,390
that's the gist of it.

314
00:16:27,320 --> 00:16:28,460
Is that really what happened?

315
00:16:35,130 --> 00:16:36,130
Goodness.

316
00:16:38,600 --> 00:16:40,640
How dare you stab me in the back...

317
00:16:40,640 --> 00:16:42,210
when I protected you
and your mother's secret?

318
00:16:42,340 --> 00:16:44,580
What are you doing to my daughter?
Get your hands off her!

319
00:16:44,580 --> 00:16:47,380
Stab you in the back?
No, it's a misunderstanding, ma'am.

320
00:16:47,910 --> 00:16:49,950
You must have wanted to show off
your reporter friend.

321
00:16:50,910 --> 00:16:52,280
But Jin Hong Ju,
you'd better get this straight.

322
00:16:52,580 --> 00:16:54,820
I won't just stop at
some pathetic little scoop.

323
00:16:55,250 --> 00:16:57,390
I can do anything I want
with this photo, you get it?

324
00:16:58,190 --> 00:16:59,190
Yes.

325
00:17:00,160 --> 00:17:02,330
What do you need me to do?

326
00:17:02,490 --> 00:17:04,860
- Goodness.
- Now we're getting somewhere.

327
00:17:05,500 --> 00:17:07,930
- Find Oh Jang Mi. Now.
- What?

328
00:17:08,330 --> 00:17:09,700
You want me to find Oh Jang Mi?

329
00:17:10,030 --> 00:17:12,340
She's probably hiding out
in some rehab hospital.

330
00:17:12,800 --> 00:17:13,970
Don't look at the big ones.

331
00:17:13,970 --> 00:17:16,310
Focus on smaller, well-equipped places.

332
00:17:17,110 --> 00:17:18,110
Got it?

333
00:17:35,390 --> 00:17:37,530
I hate tofu. Why is everything tofu?

334
00:17:37,590 --> 00:17:40,000
Are you trying to make fun of me
for getting out of jail or something?

335
00:17:40,400 --> 00:17:42,470
Mom, just stop complaining and eat.

336
00:17:43,070 --> 00:17:45,970
Geum Soon made all of this for you.

337
00:17:46,300 --> 00:17:48,070
They say if you don't eat tofu,
you'll go right back to jail.

338
00:17:48,240 --> 00:17:51,040
I already ate some when I got out.
You can eat it all.

339
00:17:51,140 --> 00:17:53,240
She goes to all this trouble for you,
and you're complaining?

340
00:17:53,510 --> 00:17:56,050
- There's a limit to your ungratefulness.
- CEO Chae.

341
00:17:56,480 --> 00:17:59,420
How dare you act like that in front of me?

342
00:17:59,780 --> 00:18:02,490
Do you have any idea how much
you've damaged the company's stock price?

343
00:18:02,620 --> 00:18:04,420
You should be on your knees
begging for forgiveness.

344
00:18:04,820 --> 00:18:06,690
And instead you're picking a fight
with Seo Rin?

345
00:18:08,030 --> 00:18:09,160
I'm sorry, Father.

346
00:18:09,760 --> 00:18:12,960
Mom probably didn't get to eat
any decent food in jail,

347
00:18:13,300 --> 00:18:14,400
so I guess she's just not hungry.

348
00:18:14,470 --> 00:18:17,570
Keep talking to your mother
with that tone, why don't you?

349
00:18:22,270 --> 00:18:23,440
Why is this tofu so delicious?

350
00:18:25,110 --> 00:18:26,110
It's so savory.

351
00:18:58,380 --> 00:19:00,440
(CEO Chae Hwa Young)

352
00:19:00,780 --> 00:19:02,550
Hello, CEO Chae.

353
00:19:02,810 --> 00:19:04,250
You know Mr. Noh Cheol Bong, right?

354
00:19:04,780 --> 00:19:07,320
I'm Shin Ae Ran. Cheol Bong's girlfriend.

355
00:19:07,820 --> 00:19:08,890
Noh Cheol Bong?

356
00:19:09,420 --> 00:19:10,420
Who's that?

357
00:19:10,590 --> 00:19:14,120
How can you not even know the name
of the man who went to jail for you?

358
00:19:15,290 --> 00:19:16,330
Ssangkal?

359
00:19:17,090 --> 00:19:19,960
Jang Mi, they're saying Ssangkal
has already been arrested.

360
00:19:20,130 --> 00:19:21,600
The investigation's already over?

361
00:19:22,030 --> 00:19:23,900
I know, right? It seems way too fast.

362
00:19:24,400 --> 00:19:26,500
I think I need to go see Ssangkal first.

363
00:19:26,740 --> 00:19:28,610
Then I'll go and rattle
Chae Hwa Young's cage.

364
00:19:34,880 --> 00:19:36,110
What is it you want?

365
00:19:36,750 --> 00:19:37,780
Money?

366
00:19:41,050 --> 00:19:43,120
My Cheol Bong said that
when you got out of prison,

367
00:19:43,620 --> 00:19:46,960
you'd give him another bag of cash.

368
00:19:47,690 --> 00:19:48,930
I'm here to collect.

369
00:19:49,390 --> 00:19:51,230
Did you think I wouldn't take care of it
if you just waited?

370
00:19:51,860 --> 00:19:53,630
How dare you show up here to collect it?

371
00:19:54,330 --> 00:19:55,930
Do you think this is
your personal playground?

372
00:19:56,370 --> 00:19:58,600
Leave here now and wait.

373
00:19:58,800 --> 00:20:00,240
I'll send Manager Lee to you.

374
00:20:00,740 --> 00:20:01,840
But, ma'am,

375
00:20:04,510 --> 00:20:06,840
when are you going to get
my Cheol Bong out of jail?

376
00:20:07,880 --> 00:20:09,210
That was part of the deal, wasn't it?

377
00:20:10,150 --> 00:20:12,220
Take that up with Manager Lee.

378
00:20:14,420 --> 00:20:15,590
Hold on a minute.

379
00:20:29,630 --> 00:20:31,540
You know, my Cheol Bong told me something.

380
00:20:32,900 --> 00:20:35,740
You'd understand better
if I used Ssangkal instead, right?

381
00:20:36,670 --> 00:20:37,740
Ssangkal?

382
00:20:38,540 --> 00:20:41,280
I was told that if you didn't pay up,

383
00:20:41,350 --> 00:20:42,580
I should go find...

384
00:20:43,450 --> 00:20:45,320
a woman named Oh Jang Mi.

385
00:20:46,920 --> 00:20:48,690
Are you threatening me?

386
00:20:53,160 --> 00:20:55,860
This Oh Jang Mi must be your weak spot.

387
00:21:01,370 --> 00:21:02,370
Goodness.

388
00:21:02,970 --> 00:21:04,230
You have company.

389
00:21:08,740 --> 00:21:11,270
Manager Lee will be in touch. Just wait.

390
00:21:16,510 --> 00:21:17,510
Fine.

391
00:21:24,790 --> 00:21:26,260
This is getting interesting now.

392
00:21:34,500 --> 00:21:35,500
Wait.

393
00:21:38,740 --> 00:21:40,570
What? What's going on?

394
00:21:40,870 --> 00:21:41,870
Oh Jang Mi.

395
00:21:42,840 --> 00:21:45,040
How do you feel about
General Manager Kang Jun Ho?

396
00:21:45,980 --> 00:21:48,050
General Manager Kang said
he wants to marry you.

397
00:21:48,750 --> 00:21:51,880
Are you nuts? I already said I wouldn't.

398
00:21:57,120 --> 00:21:58,220
The nerve of that girl.

399
00:22:05,960 --> 00:22:06,960
Manager Lee.

400
00:22:07,260 --> 00:22:09,870
Ssangkal's girlfriend was here.
Find her, now.

401
00:22:10,130 --> 00:22:11,840
And don't let Oh Jang Mi see her.

402
00:22:22,180 --> 00:22:23,350
Where did she go?

403
00:22:25,820 --> 00:22:26,850
Oh Jang Mi?

404
00:22:31,690 --> 00:22:32,690
Fancy meeting you here.

405
00:22:35,360 --> 00:22:36,360
Hold on a second.

406
00:22:58,650 --> 00:23:00,880
(Withdrawal from Yeom San Wol's account:
1,000,000 dollars)

407
00:23:01,050 --> 00:23:04,990
Maybe I'll withdraw some cash
and buy a few purses today.

408
00:23:11,160 --> 00:23:13,660
(Unable to process transfer
from this account at this time)

409
00:23:17,200 --> 00:23:18,200
What the...

410
00:23:18,200 --> 00:23:19,740
(Unable to process transfer
from this account at this time)

411
00:23:19,740 --> 00:23:21,910
Is it doing this to me on purpose?

412
00:23:22,810 --> 00:23:25,640
It's like it knows
I'm terrible with phones.

413
00:23:28,680 --> 00:23:32,180
This isn't working.
I'd better go ask Tae Pyung.

414
00:23:34,080 --> 00:23:35,090
See you later.

415
00:23:40,720 --> 00:23:43,060
Tae Pyung, could you take a look
at this for me?

416
00:23:43,360 --> 00:23:45,760
- The cryptocurrency app.
- Hi there, San Wol.

417
00:23:46,130 --> 00:23:48,630
It's already gone up a lot, right?
Let's see what we've got.

418
00:23:49,330 --> 00:23:50,600
Alright.

419
00:23:50,600 --> 00:23:52,500
What? That's strange.

420
00:23:52,870 --> 00:23:53,870
What's wrong with this thing?

421
00:23:53,940 --> 00:23:56,370
What's wrong?
Can't you get it to withdraw money either?

422
00:23:57,370 --> 00:23:58,840
What do I do?

423
00:23:59,210 --> 00:24:01,410
What about yours, Tae Pyung? Does it work?

424
00:24:01,480 --> 00:24:03,710
I don't usually hold on
to one type of cryptocurrency for long.

425
00:24:03,980 --> 00:24:07,380
A few days ago, I sold all of this coin
and switched to another one.

426
00:24:08,450 --> 00:24:10,820
It was working fine then. How strange.

427
00:24:11,250 --> 00:24:13,790
Sometimes they're down
for site maintenance or what have you.

428
00:24:14,260 --> 00:24:15,260
Right.

429
00:24:17,290 --> 00:24:20,900
- Yes, this is Suk Hee's Side Dish Shop.
- That's weird. Why won't this work?

430
00:24:23,370 --> 00:24:24,400
Alright.

431
00:24:29,070 --> 00:24:30,110
What?

432
00:24:30,510 --> 00:24:33,640
Mrs. Yeom sold one percent of her shares?

433
00:24:33,780 --> 00:24:34,810
Yes, Chairman.

434
00:24:34,880 --> 00:24:37,880
Has that woman lost her mind?

435
00:24:38,450 --> 00:24:40,580
I go to the trouble of giving it to her,
and she just sells it off?

436
00:24:40,780 --> 00:24:43,620
But I don't think you need to worry,
Chairman.

437
00:24:45,660 --> 00:24:46,660
What's that?

438
00:24:54,700 --> 00:24:56,170
My Seo Rin...

439
00:24:56,730 --> 00:24:59,470
bought Mrs. Yeom's one percent stake,
is that it?

440
00:25:02,540 --> 00:25:04,110
That's my girl.

441
00:25:04,240 --> 00:25:05,980
Look how sharp she is.

442
00:25:06,210 --> 00:25:08,510
The apple doesn't fall far from the tree.

443
00:25:10,880 --> 00:25:12,650
My goodness.

444
00:25:13,380 --> 00:25:15,590
- What do I do!
- I'm home.

445
00:25:15,790 --> 00:25:16,790
Oh dear.

446
00:25:17,750 --> 00:25:18,760
What's wrong, Mom?

447
00:25:20,320 --> 00:25:22,130
Hong Ju.

448
00:25:23,090 --> 00:25:26,800
I sold that one percent stake
that the Chairman gave me...

449
00:25:27,130 --> 00:25:29,230
to buy crypto, and...

450
00:25:29,230 --> 00:25:31,400
What? You invested in crypto?

451
00:25:33,440 --> 00:25:37,040
And? Don't tell me you lost it all.

452
00:25:38,380 --> 00:25:40,010
It's just my luck.

453
00:25:40,640 --> 00:25:42,110
It's completely worthless now.

454
00:25:42,680 --> 00:25:45,650
I lost every penny.

455
00:25:46,120 --> 00:25:48,990
What am I going to do?

456
00:25:49,050 --> 00:25:50,050
What do I do?

457
00:25:50,050 --> 00:25:53,260
- No, my money...
- This can't be happening!

458
00:25:54,190 --> 00:25:55,260
(RoboCoin, promising a ten-time return...)

459
00:25:55,330 --> 00:25:56,590
What do I do? What do I do?

460
00:25:56,660 --> 00:25:57,730
(Police Warn of Rising Crypto Scams)

461
00:25:57,790 --> 00:26:01,870
Mom, is this what you invested in?

462
00:26:03,730 --> 00:26:06,200
Mom, what were you thinking?

463
00:26:06,570 --> 00:26:08,740
I can't deal with this!

464
00:26:10,040 --> 00:26:11,470
What am I going to do?

465
00:26:12,280 --> 00:26:15,410
My nest egg! My precious money!

466
00:26:15,780 --> 00:26:18,380
What do I do?

467
00:26:19,450 --> 00:26:21,990
You're driving me crazy, Mom! I swear!

468
00:26:23,090 --> 00:26:25,620
Did Noh Cheol Bong tell you
to come find me?

469
00:26:26,020 --> 00:26:28,760
- I'm not sure.
- You said you were Shin Ae Ran, right?

470
00:26:29,590 --> 00:26:33,530
I'm sure he gave you something
when he told you to find me.

471
00:26:33,600 --> 00:26:34,600
What was it?

472
00:26:35,600 --> 00:26:37,830
- There was nothing like that.
- I heard all about it.

473
00:26:38,200 --> 00:26:41,370
He told you to find me if Chae Hwa Young
tried anything funny, didn't he?

474
00:26:41,740 --> 00:26:45,040
Which means Ssangkal
must have left you something.

475
00:26:45,340 --> 00:26:47,810
- I don't know what you're talking about.
- Ms. Shin.

476
00:26:48,210 --> 00:26:50,410
Your boyfriend is in danger right now.

477
00:26:51,180 --> 00:26:53,050
Do you really think CEO Chae would risk...

478
00:26:53,050 --> 00:26:54,920
getting Ssangkal out of prison?

479
00:26:55,250 --> 00:26:56,250
Not a chance.

480
00:26:56,520 --> 00:26:58,290
If anything,
she'll try to silence him for good.

481
00:26:58,390 --> 00:27:01,360
That's right. He might never see
the light of day again.

482
00:27:01,420 --> 00:27:03,060
He's in real danger.

483
00:27:06,900 --> 00:27:08,730
He's in prison. How can he be in danger?

484
00:27:08,730 --> 00:27:10,770
It's even more dangerous on the inside.

485
00:27:15,510 --> 00:27:16,510
Make sure you call us.

486
00:27:24,050 --> 00:27:26,850
(Suk Hee's Side Dishes)

487
00:27:35,290 --> 00:27:39,300
This morning, a group fight broke out
among inmates at Seoul Detention Center,

488
00:27:39,360 --> 00:27:41,260
resulting in the death
of Mr. Noh Cheol Bong.

489
00:27:41,530 --> 00:27:43,000
- Last January, Mr. Noh...
- Noh Cheol Bong?

490
00:27:43,070 --> 00:27:44,930
murdered a man named Oh
in Dream Hotel's parking garage,

491
00:27:45,000 --> 00:27:47,140
- What? That's Ssangkal.
- leaving the body in the street,

492
00:27:47,140 --> 00:27:48,370
and was arrested.

493
00:27:48,840 --> 00:27:51,710
Mr. Noh was rushed to a nearby hospital
after the fight...

494
00:27:51,710 --> 00:27:53,510
- but was pronounced dead.
- Ssangkal is...

495
00:27:54,440 --> 00:27:55,480
dead?

496
00:28:21,910 --> 00:28:23,410
(The First Man)

497
00:28:23,410 --> 00:28:27,310
I think CEO Chae had him killed
to cover her tracks.

498
00:28:27,540 --> 00:28:29,510
Surely she wouldn't go that far.

499
00:28:29,580 --> 00:28:31,150
The truth will come out eventually.

500
00:28:31,480 --> 00:28:33,180
Baek Ho might be right.

501
00:28:33,580 --> 00:28:35,690
Here are the medical records
you requested for Seo Rin.

502
00:28:36,090 --> 00:28:38,890
Oh Jang Mi. Now you're going to pay.

503
00:28:39,190 --> 00:28:41,120
Are the allegations about you
administering sleeping pills true?

504
00:28:41,220 --> 00:28:43,190
No. That's not true.

505
00:28:43,460 --> 00:28:45,160
General Manager Kang,
what brings you here?

506
00:28:45,500 --> 00:28:47,360
Unbelievable. A wedding announcement?

507
00:28:47,430 --> 00:28:49,830
What does Jun Ho see
in someone like Oh Jang Mi?

508
00:28:51,400 --> 00:28:53,400
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
